  {
    "id": "238",
    "title": "238. Product of Array Except Self",
    "difficulty": "Medium",
    "description": "Given an integer array nums, return an array answer such that answer[i] is equal to the product of all the elements of nums except nums[i].\n\nThe product of any prefix or suffix of nums is guaranteed to fit in a 32-bit integer.\n\nYou must write an algorithm that runs in O(n) time and without using the division operation.",
    "examples": "Example 1:\n```\nInput: nums = [1,2,3,4]\nOutput: [24,12,8,6]\n```\nExample 2:\n```\nInput: nums = [-1,1,0,-3,3]\nOutput: [0,0,9,0,0]\n ```",
    "constraints": "Constraints:\n\n- 2 <= nums.length <= 105\n- -30 <= nums[i] <= 30\n- The product of any prefix or suffix of nums is guaranteed to fit in a 32-bit integer.\n\n### Follow up: Can you solve the problem in O(1) extra space complexity? (The output array does not count as extra space for space complexity analysis.)",
    "concept": "使用前綴積（prefix product）與後綴積（suffix product）兩次遍歷，避免使用除法：\n\n1. **第一次遍歷（從左到右）**：`res[i]` 先存 `i` 左邊所有元素的乘積（`res[0] = 1`）。\n2. **第二次遍歷（從右到左）**：用變數 `postfix` 累積右邊的乘積，再乘進 `res[i]`。\n\n這樣 `res[i]` 最終等於左側乘積 × 右側乘積，即除了自身以外所有元素的乘積。\n\n時間複雜度：O(n)，空間複雜度：O(1)（輸出陣列不計入）。",
    "puzzle": {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "id": "238_0",
          "code": "res = [1] * (len(nums))",
          "originalIndent": 0
        },
        {
          "id": "238_1",
          "code": "prefix = 1",
          "originalIndent": 0
        },
        {
          "id": "238_2",
          "code": "for i in range(len(nums)):",
          "originalIndent": 0
        },
        {
          "id": "238_3",
          "code": "res[i] = prefix",
          "originalIndent": 1
        },
        {
          "id": "238_4",
          "code": "prefix *= nums[i]",
          "originalIndent": 1
        },
        {
          "id": "238_5",
          "code": "postfix = 1",
          "originalIndent": 0
        },
        {
          "id": "238_6",
          "code": "for i in range(len(nums) - 1, -1, -1):",
          "originalIndent": 0
        },
        {
          "id": "238_7",
          "code": "res[i] *= postfix",
          "originalIndent": 1
        },
        {
          "id": "238_8",
          "code": "postfix *= nums[i]",
          "originalIndent": 1
        },
        {
          "id": "238_9",
          "code": "return res",
          "originalIndent": 0
        }
      ],
      "correctOrderIds": [
        "238_0",
        "238_1",
        "238_2",
        "238_3",
